text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia hippuroides is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Lycopodiifoliae. It is native to an area in the Kimberley region of Western Australia.The diffuse, spreading shrub typically grows to a height of 0.3 to 1.6 metres (1 to 5 ft). It blooms from March to October and produces yellow flowers.
